1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with relay selection and power allocation in a multiple access relay channel, which is a common topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The proposed scheme is applicable in cellular network systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the performance improvement of the system by optimal power allocation, which is a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with transmission of information from multiple sources, which can be considered as a multimedia application. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves simulation and optimization of the system, which can be categorized under computational engineering.
